---
/**
 * Minor Ailments — Ontario Pharmacist Expanded Scope
 * Route: /services/minor-ailments/
 * Purpose: capture patients who'd otherwise go to a walk-in clinic for 13 common conditions.
 * Ontario pharmacists can now independently assess and prescribe for 13 minor ailments.
 * Source: Ontario Regulation 202/94 (as amended) — Pharmacy Act
 * OCP compliance note: list only conditions explicitly authorized under ON regulation;
 *   do not imply unlimited prescribing authority.
 */
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PhoneLink from '../../components/PhoneLink.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Minor Ailments Treatment — No Doctor Needed | Four Winds Roots Pharmacy, North York"
  description="Ontario pharmacists can now treat 13 common minor ailments — no doctor or walk-in visit required. Four Winds Roots Pharmacy, Keele & Finch, North York. Call (416) 398-8200."
  noAnalytics={true}
>
  <div class="container section">

    <h1>Minor Ailments Treatment at Your Pharmacy</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Your Ontario pharmacist can now assess and prescribe for 13 common conditions —
      no walk-in clinic, no doctor's referral required. Same-day care, right at Keele &amp; Finch.
    </p>

    <!--
      CONTENT TODOS — confirm with owner before publishing (OCP compliance):
      1. Confirm which of the 13 authorized conditions the pharmacy actively treats
      2. Confirm appointment vs. walk-in availability for minor ailments assessments
      3. Confirm any fees (most are OHIP-covered or free — verify with owner)
      4. Add booking/call CTA (Jane App or phone)
      5. OCP compliance review before publishing any prescribing claims
    -->

    <section aria-labelledby="ailments-what">
      <h2 id="ailments-what">What Can a Pharmacist Treat?</h2>
      <p>
        Under Ontario's expanded pharmacist scope, your pharmacist at Four Winds Roots can
        independently assess and treat the following minor ailments:
      </p>
      <!--
        Ontario's 13 authorized minor ailments (confirmed by OCP):
        Tick the ones the owner confirms offering — do not publish the full list
        without confirmation, as scope may expand and fee structures vary.
      -->
      <ul class="ailments-list">
        <li>Allergic rhinitis (seasonal allergies)</li>
        <li>Candidal stomatitis (oral thrush)</li>
        <li>Conjunctivitis (pink eye) — bacterial, allergic, or viral</li>
        <li>Dermatitis — atopic, contact, or seborrheic</li>
        <li>Dysmenorrhea (menstrual cramps)</li>
        <li>Gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD / heartburn)</li>
        <li>Hemorrhoids</li>
        <li>Herpes labialis (cold sores)</li>
        <li>Impetigo</li>
        <li>Insect bites and urticaria (hives)</li>
        <li>Musculoskeletal sprains and strains</li>
        <li>Tick bites — Lyme disease prophylaxis</li>
        <li>Urinary tract infections (UTIs) — uncomplicated, in adults</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="ailments-note">
        <em>
          <!-- TODO: confirm with owner which of these are actively offered -->
          TODO: Add "We offer [X] of these services — call to confirm availability"
          or list only the confirmed subset. Do not publish this full list without
          owner sign-off and OCP compliance review.
        </em>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="ailments-how">
      <h2 id="ailments-how">How It Works</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Call us or walk in — no appointment needed for most conditions.</li>
        <li>Your pharmacist conducts a brief private assessment.</li>
        <li>
          If appropriate, they prescribe a treatment on the spot — no wait, no referral.
        </li>
        <li>
          If the condition is outside pharmacist scope, we refer you to the right provider.
        </li>
      </ol>
      <!-- TODO: confirm walk-in vs. appointment policy with owner -->
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="ailments-holistic">
      <h2 id="ailments-holistic">Whole-Person Care, Not Just a Prescription</h2>
      <p>
        At Four Winds Roots, minor ailment assessments are part of our holistic care model.
        Your pharmacist reviews your full medication and supplement profile before prescribing,
        so your treatment fits your whole health picture — not just the symptom in front of them.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="/holistic-wellness">Learn about our holistic wellness approach &rarr;</a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="ailments-book">
      <h2 id="ailments-book">Get Seen Today</h2>
      <p>Walk in or call — most minor ailment assessments are same-day.</p>
      <div class="ailments-ctas">
        <PhoneLink class="btn btn-call" display="Call (416) 398-8200" />
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-secondary">Hours &amp; Location</a>
      </div>
      <!-- TODO: add Jane App booking widget once confirmed with owner -->
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .lead {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  section + section {
    margin-top: var(--space-10);
    padding-top: var(--space-10);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .ailments-list {
    columns: 2;
    column-gap: var(--space-8);
    margin-block: var(--space-4);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .ailments-list { columns: 1; }
  }

  .ailments-list li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    break-inside: avoid;
  }

  .ailments-note {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
  }

  ol {
    padding-left: var(--space-5);
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .ailments-ctas {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
  }
</style>
